# Security

## Auth & AuthZ

- Supabase Auth for identity; RLS for data access
- Verify org membership on every mutation — UI hiding is not security
- Role checks (`owner`, `admin`, `member`) for destructive org actions

## Secrets

- All keys in env vars (see `.env.example`); never commit `.env*`
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` server-only; never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`
- Rotate keys via provider dashboards, not code

## Input validation

- Zod on all API/Action inputs
- Sanitize user HTML if rich text is added later
- Reject path traversal in storage uploads; validate MIME types

## AI safety

- Do not send secrets or PII in prompts
- Hash prompts in `ai_generations.prompt_hash` for audit
- Cap token usage per org; timeout long generations

## Payments

- Verify Stripe webhook signatures
- Never trust client-side payment state; confirm via webhook + DB

## Headers & CSP

- Use Next.js security headers in production
- Sentry scrubs PII from error reports

## Forbidden

- Bypassing RLS with service role in user requests
- `eval`, dynamic `require`, shell execution with user input
- Logging tokens, passwords, or full auth cookies
